1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,716
Here is how I automated my morning routine

2
00:00:03,716 --> 00:00:07,787
all of it runs while I am still hitting snooze

3
00:00:07,787 --> 00:00:12,034
First, a script pulls my calendar and to-do list

4
00:00:12,034 --> 00:00:17,077
then it picks the three things that actually matter today

5
00:00:17,077 --> 00:00:19,997
It fires off a smart-plug command

6
00:00:19,997 --> 00:00:26,722
so my coffee starts brewing five minutes before I even walk into the kitchen

7
00:00:26,722 --> 00:00:31,765
Then it records a 30-second voice note summarizing my day

8
00:00:31,765 --> 00:00:34,951
and sends it to my own messaging app

9
00:00:34,951 --> 00:00:36,986
Three small automations

10
00:00:36,986 --> 00:00:37,871
That is it

11
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:42,029
But it saves me 20 minutes every single morning

12
00:00:42,029 --> 00:00:44,861
I used to wake up already behind

13
00:00:44,861 --> 00:00:46,896
Now I wake up caught up

14
00:00:46,896 --> 00:00:49,993
The whole thing is a 40-line script

15
00:00:49,993 --> 00:00:54,594
I will link it in the comments if you want to try it

16
00:00:54,594 --> 00:00:58,487
Seriously go automate one thing this weekend

17
00:00:58,487 --> 00:01:03,000
Future you will be annoyed you did not do it sooner

